    <media alt="An illustration shows five reactions of an acid derivative. The structure of acid derivative is highlighted and shows a carbonyl group bonded to R and green Y. Hydrolysis yields RCOOH. Alcoholysis with R’OH yields RCOOR’. Aminolysis with ammonia yields RCONH2. Reduction yields RCHO that further yields RCH2OH. Grignard reaction with R’ MgX yields RCOR’ that further reacts with R’ MgX to yield RCR’R’OH. The carbonyl oxygen atoms are highlighted in pink. OR’ amino group hydrogen atoms are highlighted in blue.">
